<font color="#FF0000">FIGHTING NO MORE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 26 20:59:11 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
This is a wonderful site.  I am married to a Vietnam vet (medic) although I met him after his service.  I have read at least 12 books (fiction and non-fiction) and seen practically every movie on this war and I am a history major and YET I know nothing.  Even if I went to visit Vietnam today, I would still know nothing.  Vietnam is a war that must be studied and restudied and never forgotten until we get it right.  In other words, until we fight no more forever.  Thanks.
